      "id": "assistant-1775059517625-50dhx4",
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Because `STORYBOARD.json` is not the shot list.\n\nIt only exists to declare the image references used to generate the single storyboard board image. In this setup, the actual shot-by-shot content lives in `STORYBOARD.md`, while `STORYBOARD.json` just tells the board generator what reference images to include, starting with the required storyboard template image.\n\nSo this is expected:\n\n- `STORYBOARD.md` = the actual shots, action, framing, progression\n- `STORYBOARD.json` = board-generation references only\n- `STORYBOARD.png` = the rendered review board\n\nRight now your `STORYBOARD.json` contains only the required template reference because no additional source images have been attached yet.\n\nIf you want, I can show you the full storyboard shot list next so you can inspect the actual scene plan rather than the board metadata."
